There are two query cache-related options that may be
specified in a @code{SELECT} statement:

@findex SQL_CACHE
@findex SQL_NO_CACHE

@table @code

@item SQL_CACHE
The query result is cached if the value of the @code{query_cache_type}
system variable is @code{ON} or @code{DEMAND}.

@item SQL_NO_CACHE
