Logical OR.
Evaluates to @code{1} if any operand is non-zero,
to @code{NULL} if any operand is @code{NULL},
otherwise @code{0} is returned.
@c end_description_for_help_topic

@c example_for_help_topic ||
@example
mysql> SELECT 1 || 1;
        -> 1
mysql> SELECT 1 || 0;
        -> 1
mysql> SELECT 0 || 0;
        -> 0
mysql> SELECT 0 || NULL;
        -> NULL
mysql> SELECT 1 || NULL;
        -> 1
@end example

