Make @code{LOCK TABLE} aware of InnoDB row-level locks. (Bug #3299)

@item
Fixed race conditions in SHOW INNODB STATUS. (Bug #3596)
@end itemize


@node InnoDB news-4.0.19, InnoDB news-4.0.18, InnoDB news-4.0.20, InnoDB change history
@appendixsubsec MySQL/InnoDB-4.0.19, May 4, 2004

Functionality added or changed:

@itemize @bullet
@item
Better error message when the server has to crash because the buffer
pool is exhausted by the lock table or the adaptive hash index.

@item
Print always the count of pending @code{pread()} and @code{pwrite()}
calls if there is a long semaphore wait.

@item
Improve space utilization when rows of 1,500 to 8,000 bytes are
inserted in the order of the primary key.

@item
Remove potential buffer overflow errors by sending diagnostic output to
stderr or files instead of stdout or fixed-size memory buffers.  As a
side effect, the output of @code{SHOW INNODB STATUS} will be written
to a file @file{@var{<datadir>}/innodb.status.@var{<pid>}} every 15
seconds.
@end itemize

Bugs fixed:

@itemize @bullet
@item
Fixed a bug: @code{DROP DATABASE} did not work if @code{FOREIGN KEY}
references were defined within the database. (Bug #3058)

@item
Remove unnecessary files, functions and variables.  Many of these were
needed in the standalone version of InnoDB.  Remove debug functions
and variables from non-debug build.

@item
Add diagnostic code to analyze an assertion failure in ha_innodb.cc on line
2020 reported by a user. (Bug #2903)

@item
Fixed a bug: in a @code{FOREIGN KEY}, @code{ON UPDATE CASCADE}
was not triggered if the update changed a string to another value
identical in alphabetical ordering, e.g., @samp{abc} -> @samp{aBc}.

@item
Protect the reading of the latest foreign key error explanation buffer
with a mutex; in theory, a race condition could cause @code{SHOW
INNODB STATUS} print garbage characters after the error info.

@item
Fixed a bug: The row count and key cardinality estimate was grossly
too small if each clustered index page only contained one record.

@item
Parse @code{CONSTRAINT FOREIGN KEY} correctly. (Bug #3332)

@item
Fixed a memory corruption bug on Windows.  The bug is present in all
InnoDB versions in Windows, but it depends on how the linker places a
static array in @code{srv0srv.c}, whether the bug shows itself. 4
bytes were overwritten with a pointer to a statically allocated
string @samp{get windows aio return value}.

@item
Fix a glitch reported by Philippe Lewicki on the general mailing list:
do not print a warning to the @file{.err} log if @code{read_key} fails
with a lock wait timeout error 146.

@item
Allow quotes to be embedded in strings in the private SQL parser of
InnoDB, so that @samp{'} can be used in InnoDB table and column names.
Display quotes within identifiers properly.

@item
Debugging: Allow @code{UNIV_SYNC_DEBUG} to be disabled while
@code{UNIV_DEBUG} is enabled.

@item
Debugging: Handle magic numbers in a more consistent way.
@end itemize


@node InnoDB news-4.0.18, InnoDB news-5.0.0, InnoDB news-4.0.19, InnoDB change history
@appendixsubsec MySQL/InnoDB-4.0.18, February 13, 2004

@itemize @bullet
@item
Do not allow dropping a table referenced by a @code{FOREIGN KEY}
constraint, unless the user does @code{SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS=0}.
The error message here is somewhat misleading
``Cannot delete or update a parent row...'', and must be changed in a
future version 4.1.x.
@item
Make @code{InnoDB} to remember the @code{CONSTRAINT} name given by a user for
a @code{FOREIGN KEY}.
@item
Change the print format of @code{FOREIGN KEY} constraints spanning
multiple databases to @code{`db_name`.`tbl_name`}. But when
parsing them, we must also accept @code{`db_name.tbl_name`},
because that was the output format in < 4.0.18.
@item
An optimization in locking: If @code{AUTOCOMMIT=1}, then we do not
need to make a plain @code{SELECT} set shared locks even on the
@code{SERIALIZABLE} isolation level, because we know that the
transaction is read-only. A read-only transaction can always be
performed on the @code{REPEATABLE READ} level, and that does not
endanger the serializability.
@item
Implement an automatic downgrade from >= 4.1.1 -> 4.0.18 if the user
has not created tables in @file{.ibd} files or used other 4.1.x
features. @strong{Consult} the manual section on
@strong{multiple tablespaces} carefully if you want to downgrade!
@item
Fixed a bug: MySQL should not allow @code{REPLACE} to internally
perform an @code{UPDATE} if the table is referenced by a
@code{FOREIGN KEY}. The MySQL manual states that @code{REPLACE} must
resolve a duplicate-key error semantically with
@code{DELETE}(s) + @code{INSERT}, and not by an @code{UPDATE}.
In versions < 4.0.18 and < 4.1.2, MySQL could resolve a duplicate key
conflict in @code{REPLACE} by doing an @code{UPDATE} on the existing
row, and @code{FOREIGN KEY} checks could behave in a semantically
wrong way. (Bug #2418)
@item
Fixed a bug: generate @code{FOREIGN KEY} constraint identifiers
locally for each table, in the form
@code{db_name/tbl_name_ibfk_number}. If the user gives the
constraint name explicitly, then remember it. These changes should
ensure that foreign key id's in a slave are the same as in the master,
and @code{DROP FOREIGN KEY} does not break replication. (Bug #2167)
@item
Fixed a bug: allow quoting of identifiers in InnoDB's
@code{FOREIGN KEY} definitions with a backtick (`) and a double quote
("). You can now use also spaces in table and column names, if you
quote the identifiers. (Bug #1725) and (Bug #2424)
@item
Fixed a bug: @code{FOREIGN KEY ... ON UPDATE/DELETE NO ACTION} must
check the foreign key constraint, not ignore it. Since we do not have
deferred constraints in @code{InnoDB}, this bugfix makes @code{InnoDB} to check
@code{NO ACTION} constraints immediately, like it checks
@code{RESTRICT} constraints.
@item
Fixed a bug: @code{InnoDB} crashed in @code{RENAME TABLE} if 
@code{'db_name.tbl_name'} is shorter than 5 characters.
(Bug #2689)
@item
Fixed a bug: in @code{SHOW TABLE STATUS}, @code{InnoDB} row count and index
cardinality estimates wrapped around at 512 million in 32-bit
computers. Note that unless MySQL is compiled with the
@code{BIG_TABLES} option, they will still wrap around at 4 billion.
@item
Fixed a bug: If there was a @code{UNIQUE} secondary index, and
@code{NULL} values in that unique index, then with the
@code{IS NULL} predicate, @code{InnoDB} returned only the first matching row,
though there can be many.
This bug was introduced in 4.0.16. (Bug #2483)
@end itemize


